This problems is about using sliding window to get the maximum sum when a set of elements are in a window and we return the maxSum value we get.


Kadane's Algorithm is used to find the maximum sum of a contiguous subarray in O(n) time.
The idea is to traverse the array from left to right. At each index, we calculate the maximum subarray sum that must end at that index.
We maintain two variables:
currentMax
returnMax

currentMax
currentMax stores the maximum subarray sum ending at the current index.
For each element, we have two choices:
Continue the previous subarray by adding the current element.
Start a new subarray from the current element.
So we update:
currentMax = Math.max(nums[i], currentMax + nums[i]);
If currentMax + nums[i] is greater, we continue the existing subarray.
If nums[i] is greater, we drop the previous subarray and start fresh from the current index.

returnMax
returnMax stores the best maximum subarray sum found so far.
After updating currentMax, we update:
returnMax = Math.max(returnMax, currentMax);
At the end, returnMax contains the maximum subarray sum.

